description._content: Description: Sheet of stationery - folded lined paper, the front decorated with flowers and leaves twining around a bar in a green border surrounding the blank space. The top, bottom and open edge are scalloped. At the upper left is an oval frame inscribed in Hebrew and English, “A happy New Year.” At lower right, a scrap (man in kittle blessing boy) has been attached. Date: early 20th century Medium: Stationery, paper Repository: Yeshiva University Museum Call Number: 2001.357 Persistent URL: access.cjh.org/593556 Rights Information: No known copyright restrictions; may be subject to third party rights.
